obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35240)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35240&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the State Financial`
  line `Corporations Act, 1951.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in any State on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. 1st August, 1952 (in the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir), vide notification No. S.R.O. 1317, dated 28th`
  line `July, 1952, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35316)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35316&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Board of directors of the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "Development Bank" means the Industrial Development Bank of India established under`
  line `the Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964);]`
  line
  line `^2[(b) "Financial Corporation" means a Financial Corporation established under section 3 and`
  line `includes a Joint Financial Corporation established under section 3A;]`
  line
  line `^3[(c) "industrial concern" means any concern engaged or to be engaged in--`
  line
  line `(i) the manufacture, preservation or processing of goods;`
  line
  line `^4[(ii) mining or development of mines;]`
  line
  line `(iii) the hotel industry;`
  line
  line `(iv) the transport of passengers or goods by road or by water or by air ^5[or by ropeway or by`
  line lift];
  line
  line `(v) the generation or distribution of electricity or any other form of power;`
  line
  line `(vi) the maintenance, repair, resting or servicing of machinery of any description or vehicles`
  line `or vessels or motor boats or trailers or tractors;`
  line
  line `(vii) assembling, repairing or packing any article with the aid of machinery or power;`
  line
  line `^6[(viii) the setting up or development of an industrial area or industrial estate;]`
  line
  line `(ix) fishing or providing shore facilities for fishing or maintenance thereof; ^7***`
  line
  line `^8[(x) providing weigh bridge facilities;`
  line
  line `(xi) providing engineering, technical, financial, management, marketing or other services or`
  line `facilities for industry;`
  line
  line `(xii) providing medical, health or other allied, services;`
  line
  line `(xiii) providing software or hardware services relating to information technology,`
  line `telecommunications or electronics including satellite linkage and audio or visual cable`
  line communication;
  line
  line `(xiv) setting up or development of tourism related facilities including amusement parks,`
  line `convention centres, restaurants, travel and transport (including those at airports), tourist service`
  line `agencies and guidance and counselling services to the tourists;`
  line
  line `(xv) construction;`
  line
  line `(xvi) development, maintenance and construction of roads;`
  line
  line `(xvii) providing commercial complex facilities and community centres including conference`
  line halls;
  line
  line `(xviii) floriculture;`
  line
  line `(xix) tissue culture, fish culture, poultry farming, breeding and hatcheries;`
  line
  line `(xx) service industry, such as altering, ornamenting, polishing, finishing, oiling, washing,`
  line `cleaning or otherwise treating or adapting any article or substance with a view to its use, sale,`
  line `transport, delivery or disposal;`
  line
  line `(xxi) research and development of any concept, technology, design, process of product,`
  line `whether in relation to any of the matters aforesaid, including any activities approved by the Small`
  line `Industries Bank; or`
  line
  line `(xxii) such other activity as may be approved by the Small Industries Bank;]`
  line
  line `^9[Explanation 1.--The expression "processing of goods" includes any art or process for producing,`
  line `preparing or making an article by subjecting any material to a manual, mechanical, chemical, electrical or`
  line `any other like operation.]`
  line
  line `^10[Explanation 2. --If any doubt arises as to whether a concern is an industrial concern or not, the`
  line `same shall be referred to the ^11[Small Industries Bank] for its decision and the decision of the ^11[Small`
  line `Industries Bank] thereon shall be final.]`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules or regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^12[(da) the expression "public sector bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under the`
  line `State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India`
  line `(Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or under`
  line `section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980`
  line `(40 of 1980);]`
  line
  line `(e) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(f) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `^13[(fa) "Small Industries Bank" means the Small Industries Development Bank of India established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989`
  line `(39 of 1989);]`
  line
  line `^14[^15[(fb)] "State Co-operative Bank" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Clause (f) of section`
  line `2 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `^16[(fc)] "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) "underwriting" means contract, with or without conditions, to subscribe for stocks, shares,`
  line `bonds or debentures of an industrial concern with a view to the resale of the whole or any part`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 2, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 2, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for sub-clause (viii) (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `7. The word "or" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 2, for clauses (x) to (xiii) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `9. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 by Act 43 of 1985, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 2, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 2, for Clause (fb) (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `15. Clause (ff) re-lettered as clause (fb) thereof by Act 39 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `16. Clause (fff) re-lettered as clause (fc) thereof by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35317)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of State Financial Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 3, for "acquire and to hold" (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35317&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, establish a Financial Corporation for the State under such name as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name notified under sub-section (1),`
  line `having perpetual succession and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to`
  line `^1[acquire, hold and dispose of] property and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (35318)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Joint Financial Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35318&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Establishment of Joint Financial Corporations.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 3, two or more States may, after consultation with the ^2[Small Industries Bank], enter into an`
  line `agreement that there shall be one Financial Corporation for the group of States participating in the`
  line `agreement and if the agreement is published in the Official Gazette of each of those States, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Joint Financial Corporation to serve`
  line `the needs of those States under such name as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) An inter-State agreement under sub-section (1) among the participating States may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the fixation of the authorised capital of the Joint Financial Corporation, the`
  line `number of fully paid-up shares into which it shall be divided and the allocation among the`
  line `participating States of the shares to be distributed under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) provide for the sharing of the liability for me guarantee under section 6 or section 7 ^3[or`
  line `section 8];`
  line
  line `(c) provide for the number of directors to be nominated to the Board by each participating State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) provide for the apportionment among the participating States of expenditure in connection`
  line `with the Joint Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `(f) determine which of the participating State Governments shall exercise the several functions of`
  line `the State Government under this Act, and references in this Act to the State Government, in relation`
  line `to the Joint Financial Corporation, shall, save as otherwise expressly provided, be construed`
  line accordingly;
  line
  line `(g) provide for consultation among the participating States either generally or with reference to`
  line `particular matters arising under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) make such incidental and consequential provisions, not inconsistent with this Act, as may be`
  line `deemed necessary or expedient for giving effect to the agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) The Joint Financial Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name notified under`
  line `sub-section (1), having perpetual succession and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(4) Any reference in this Act to State in relation to a Joint Financial Corporation established for two`
  line `or more States, shall be construed as a reference to each such State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 24, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 43 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35319)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Share capital and share-holders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35319&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The authorised capital of the Financial Corporation shall`
  line `be such sum as may be fixed by the State Government in this behalf, but it shall not be less than fifty`
  line `lakhs of rupees or exceed five hundred crores of rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, on the recommendation of the Small Industries Bank, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, increase the authorised capital up to one thousand crores of rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 4D, the authorised capital shall be divided into such number of`
  line `fully paid-up shares of the same face value and such number of fully paid-up redeemable preference`
  line `shares of the same face value and shall be issued to the parties mentioned in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) and in the case of parties referred to in clause (d) of that sub-section, such shares shall be`
  line `issued at such times and in such manner as the State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, determine.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the approval of the State Government and the Small Industries Bank, the Board shall`
  line `determine the number of shares which may, respectively, be distributed among--`
  line
  line `(a) the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(c) public sector banks, the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956), other insurance companies owned or controlled`
  line `by the Central Government, other institutions owned or controlled by the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(d) parties other than those referred to in clause (a), or clause (b) or clause (c):`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of shares which may be allocated to parties referred to in clause (d) shall in`
  line `no case exceed forty-nine per cent. of the total number of issued equity shares:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no increase in the issued equity capital shall be made in such a manner that the`
  line `parties referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) hold in aggregate, at any time less than`
  line `fifty-one per cent. of the issued equity capital of the Financial Corporation.]`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions contained in this section, the allocation of shares among the parties`
  line `referred to in clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (3) and the allotment of such shares shall be made by the`
  line `Financial Corporation in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) If any shares allocated to any of the parties referred to in clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (3)`
  line `remain unsubscribed, they shall be subscribed for equally by the State Government and the ^3[Small`
  line `Industries Bank].]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 4, for sections (1), (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 3, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 4, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (35245)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 6
  title `Special class of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35245&sectionno=4A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^2[4A. Special class of shares.--^3[(1) The State Government may, in consultation with the ^1[Small`
  line `Industries Bank], specify from time to time such part of the unissued capital of the Financial Corporation`
  line `as shall be allocated for the issue of a special class of shares.]`
  line
  line `(2) The special class of shares so allocated under sub-section (1), shall be,--`
  line
  line `(a) divided into such number of shares of the same face value as the State Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the ^4[Small Industries Bank], determine;`
  line
  line `(b) subscribed by the State Government and the ^4[Small Industries Bank] and they may do so in`
  line `such proportion as may be agreed upon by and between them and the Financial Corporation shall`
  line `make allotment of such shares accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The funds representing the capital subscribed as aforesaid shall be used only for such purposes, in`
  line `such manner and for rendering assistance to such class or category of industrial concerns, as the ^4[Small`
  line `Industries Bank] may, in consultation with and after obtaining the advice of the State Government,`
  line `specify in this behalf from time to time and nothing contained in ^5*** section 48 shall apply thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) The rate of dividend declared on the special class of shares in respect of any accounting year of a`
  line `Financial Corporation shall not exceed the rate of dividend in respect of its other shares.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-sections (2) to (5) of section 4, section 5, and ^6[sub-sections (1) to (4) of`
  line `section 6], shall apply to the special class of shares.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 4, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 26, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 5, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "section 47" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "sub-section (1) of section 6" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (35246)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of share capital to Development Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 27 (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35246&sectionno=4B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Transfer of share capital to Development Bank .--On such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify (hereinafter referred to as the specified date), all the`
  line `shares of every Financial Corporation subscribed by the Reserve Bank as on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the specified date, shall, stand transferred to, and vested in, the Development Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_c:
  sectionId (35247)
  sectionNo 4C
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 27 (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35247&sectionno=4C&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[4C. Payment of amount.--The Reserve Bank shall be given by the Development Bank, in cash, for`
  line `the transfer to, and vesting in, the Development Bank of the shares of every Financial Corporation which`
  line `have been subscribed by the Reserve Bank, an amount equal to the face value of the shares of the`
  line `Financial Corporation so subscribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_d:
  sectionId (35248)
  sectionNo 4D
  orderNo 9
  title `Issue of redeemable preference shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35248&sectionno=4D&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[4D. Issue of redeemable preference shares.--(1) On and after the commencement of the State`
  line `Financial Corporations (Amendment) Act, 2000, the Financial Corporation may--`
  line
  line `(a) issue redeemable preference shares on such terms and in such manner as the Board may`
  line `decide; and`
  line
  line `(b) convert, such number of equity shares as it may decide into redeemable preference shares,`
  line `with the prior approval of the State Government and the Small Industries Bank, by a resolution passed`
  line `in the general meeting of the shareholers:`
  line
  line `Provided that such conversion shall in no case reduce the equity shares held by the parties referred to`
  line `in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (3) of section 4 to less than fifty-one per cent. of the issued equity`
  line `capital of the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The redeemable preference shares referred to in sub-section (1) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) carry such fixed rate of dividend as the Financial Corporation may specify at the time of such`
  line `issue or conversion; and`
  line
  line `(b) neither be transferable nor carry any voting rights.`
  line
  line `(3) The redeemable preference shares referred to in sub-section (1) shall be redeemed by the Financial`
  line `Corporation in such instalments and in such manner as the Board may determine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_e:
  sectionId (35249)
  sectionNo 4E
  orderNo 10
  title `Reduction of share capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35249&sectionno=4E&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[4E. Reduction of share capital.--(1) The Financial Corporation, with the prior approval of the State`
  line `Government and the Small Industries Bank, may, by resolution passed in a general meeting of the`
  line `shareholders, reduce its share capital in any way.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the share capital may be reduced by--`
  line
  line `(a) extinguishing or reducing the liability on any of its equity shares in respect of share capital not`
  line `paid-up; or`
  line
  line `(b) either with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its equity shares,`
  line `cancelling any paid-up share capital which is lost or is unrepresented by available assets; or`
  line
  line `(c) either with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its equity shares, paying`
  line `off any paid-up share capital which is in excess of the wants of the Financial Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_f:
  sectionId (35250)
  sectionNo 4F
  orderNo 11
  title `Restriction on exercising of voting right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35250&sectionno=4F&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[4F. Restriction on exercising of voting right.--Every shareholder of the Financial Corporation`
  line `holding equity shares shall have a right to vote in respect of such shares on every resolution and his`
  line `voting right on a poll shall be in proportion to his share of the paid-up equity capital of the Financial`
  line `Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided however, that no shareholder, other than a shareholder referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 4, shall be entitled to exercise voting rights in respect of any equity share`
  line `held by him in excess of ten per cent. of the issued equity capital.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_g:
  sectionId (35251)
  sectionNo 4G
  orderNo 12
  title `Proxy voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35251&sectionno=4G&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[4G. Proxy voting.--In a general meeting referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4D`
  line `and sub-section (1) of section 4E, the resolution for conversion or reduction of share capital shall be`
  line `passed by shareholders entitled to vote, voting in person, or, where proxies are allowed, by proxy, and the`
  line `votes cast in favour of the resolution are not less than three times the number of votes, if any, cast against`
  line `the resolution by shareholders so entitled and voting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_h:
  sectionId (35252)
  sectionNo 4H
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer of share capital to Small Industries Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35252&sectionno=4H&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_4_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[4H. Transfer of share capital to Small Industries Bank.--On such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, notify (hereinafter referred to as the notified date) all the`
  line `shares of every Financial Corporation subscribed by the Development Bank and the amount outstanding`
  line `in respect of loans in lieu of capital provided by the Development Bank as on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the notified date, shall stand transferred to, and vested in, the Small Industries Bank, such`
  line `transfer shall be at such rate and be paid in cash or such other manner as may be mutually agreed upon`
  line `between the Development Bank and the Small Industries Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35253)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 14
  title `Transfer of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35253&sectionno=5&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Transfer of shares. -- (1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the shares of the`
  line `Financial Corporation shall be freely transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall entitle the parties referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 4 to transfer any of the shares held by them in the Financial Corporation if`
  line `such transfer will result in reducing the aggregate value of shares held by them to less than fifty-one per`
  line `cent. of the issued equity capital of the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may refuse to register the transfer of any shares in the name of the transferee on any`
  line `one or more of the following grounds, and on no other ground, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer of the shares is in contravention of the provisions of the Act or regulations made`
  line `thereunder or any other law;`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer of the shares, in the opinion of the Board, is prejudicial to the interests of the`
  line `Financial Corporation or to the public interest;`
  line
  line `(c) the transfer of shares is prohibited by an order of a court, tribunal or any other authority under`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `4. The Board shall, before the expiry of two months from the date on which the instrument of transfer`
  line `of shares of the Financial Corporation is lodged with it for the purpose of registration of such transfer, not only form, in good faith, its opinion as to whether such registration ought not or ought to be refused on`
  line `any of the grounds referred to in sub-section (3) but also,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it has formed the opinion that such registration ought not to be so refused, effect such`
  line `registration; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it has formed the opinion that such registration ought to be refused on any of the grounds`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (3), intimate the transferor and the transferee by notice in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal against the order of refusal of the Board under sub-section (4) shall lie to the Central`
  line `Government and the procedure for filing and hearing of such appeal shall be in accordance with the rules`
  line `made by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35254)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 15
  title `Conversion of shares guaranteed by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35254&sectionno=6&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Conversion of shares guaranteed by State Government.--(1) On the commencement of the`
  line `State Financial Corporations (Amendment) Act, 2000, every shareholder shall be given by the Financial`
  line `Corporation an option to require the Financial Corporation to convert the shares held by him into shares`
  line `of the same nominal value without the State Government guarantee and issue fresh share certificate or to`
  line `pay the amount paid in respect of such shares not exceeding the face value of the shares held by him.`
  line
  line `(2) The option referred to in sub-section (1) shall be given by the Financial Corporation to every`
  line `existing shareholder before the expiry of three months from the commencement of the State Financial`
  line `Corporations (Amendment) Act, 2000 and shall be exercised by the shareholder within three months from`
  line `the date of receipt of such option.`
  line
  line `(3) The option exercised under sub-section (2) shall be final and shall not be altered or rescinded after`
  line `it has been exercised.`
  line
  line `(4) If, a shareholder exercises option for receiving the payment within the stipulated time, the`
  line `Financial Corporation shall, on surrender of the share certificate held by him, pay him the amount paid in`
  line `respect of such shares not exceeding the face value thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any shareholder fails to exercise the option given to him under sub-section (1), within`
  line `the time stipulated in sub-section (2), he shall be deemed to have exercised the first option.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-section (4) shall be deemed to result in reduction of the share capital and`
  line `the Financial Corporation may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 4, allot the shares`
  line `surrendered by any shareholder, to any other person.`
  line
  line `(6) The Financial Corporation shall keep at its head office a register, in one or more books, of`
  line `shareholders and shall enter therein the following particulars so far as they may be available, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the name, addresses and occupations, if any, of the shareholders and a statement of the shares`
  line `held by each shareholder, distinguishing each share by its denoting number;`
  line
  line `(ii) the date on which each person is so entered as a shareholder;`
  line
  line `(iii) the date on which any person ceases to be a shareholder; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the shares held with a depository under the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6), it shall be lawful for the Financial`
  line `Corporation to keep the register of the shareholders in computer floppies or diskettes, compact disk or any`
  line `other electronic form subject to such safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), a copy of, or`
  line `extract from, the register of shareholders, certified to be a true copy under the hand of an officer of the`
  line `Financial Corporation authorised in this behalf, shall, in all legal proceedings, be admissible in evidence.`
  line
  line `(9) The register of beneficial owners maintained by a depository under section 11 of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) shall be deemed to be a register of shareholders for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (6), (7) and (8), no notice of any trust,`
  line `express, implied or constructive, shall be entered on the register of shareholders or be receivable by the`
  line `Financial Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to a depository in respect of shares held by it as a`
  line `registered owner on behalf of a beneficial owner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-sections (6), (9) and this sub-section, the expressions`
  line `"beneficial owner", "depository" and "registered owner" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clauses (a), (e) and (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), the shares of the`
  line `Financial Corporation shall be deemed to be included among the securities enumerated in section 20 of`
  line `that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35255)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 16
  title `Additional capital of Financial Corporation and its borrowing powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35255&sectionno=7&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Additional capital of Financial Corporation and its borrowing powers.--(1) The Financial`
  line `Corporation may issue and sell bonds and debentures for the purpose of increasing its working capital.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, on a request being made to it by the Financial Corporation, guarantee`
  line `the bonds and debentures issued by the Financial Corporation as to the repayment of principal and the`
  line `payment of interest at such rate as may be fixed by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts hereinafter mentioned in this sub-section, such of`
  line `the bonds and debentures issued by the Financial Corporation as are guaranteed by the State Government`
  line `as to the repayment of the principal and payment of interest and receipts issued by it for such of deposits`
  line `as are guaranteed by the State Government as to the repayment of the principal and payment of interest`
  line `shall be deemed to be included among the securities enumerated in section 20 of the Indian Trusts Act,`
  line `1882 (2 of 1882), and also to be approved securities for the purpose of the Insurance Act, 1938`
  line `(4 of 1938). ^2***`
  line
  line `(4) The Financial Corporation may, for the purposes of carrying out its functions under this Act,`
  line `borrow money from the Reserve Bank--`
  line
  line `(a) repayable on demand or on the expiry of a fixed period not exceeding ninety days from the`
  line `date on which the money is so borrowed against the security of--`
  line
  line `(i) stocks, funds and securities (other than immovable property) in which a trustee is`
  line `authorised to invest trust money by any law for the time being in force in India, or`
  line
  line `(ii) such bills of exchange and promissory notes as are eligible for purchase or re-discount by`
  line `the Reserve Bank or as are fully guaranteed as to the repayment of the principal and payment of`
  line `interest by a State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) repayable on the expiry of a fixed period not exceeding eighteen months from the date on`
  line `which the money is so borrowed, against securities of the Central Government or of any State`
  line `Government of the maturity, or subject to the previous approval of the State Government, against`
  line `bonds and debentures issued by the Financial Corporation and maturing within a period not exceeding`
  line `eighteen months from the date on which the money is so borrowed and every such bond and`
  line `debenture shall be guaranteed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount borrowed by the Financial Corporation under clause (b) shall not at any`
  line `time exceed in the aggregate twice the paid-up share capital thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) The Financial Corporation may, for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act,`
  line `borrow money from the State Government, any financial institution, scheduled bank, insurance company`
  line `or any other person approved by the Board on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(6) The total amount of bonds and debentures issued and outstanding, the amounts borrowed by the`
  line `Financial Corporation under clause (b) of sub-section (4) and sub-section (5) and of the contingent liabilities of the Financial Corporation in the form of guarantees given by it or underwriting agreements`
  line `entered into by it, shall not exceed ten times the amount of the paid-up share capital and reserve fund of`
  line `the Financial Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Financial Corporation may, with the prior approval of the Small Industries Bank,`
  line `exceed the aforesaid limit up to thirty time the amount of the paid-up share capital and reserve fund of the`
  line `Financial Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "and the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)" omitted by Act 4 of 2013, s. 17 and the Schedule`
  line `(date to be notified).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35256)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 17
  title `Deposits with the Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35256&sectionno=8&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Deposits with Financial Corporation.--(1) The Financial Corporation may accept from the State`
  line `Government, or with the prior approval of the Reserve Bank, from a local authority or any other person`
  line `deposits repayable after the expiry of a period which shall not be less than twelve months from the date of`
  line `the making of the deposit and on such other terms as the Board thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount of such deposits shall not exceed twice the paid-up share capital of the`
  line `Financial Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may permit the Financial Corporation to accept deposits`
  line `up to a higher limit not exceeding ten times the paid-up share capital of the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any deposit accepted under sub-section (1), other than a deposit from the State Government may,`
  line `if so required by the Financial Corporation, be guaranteed by the State Government as to the repayment of`
  line `the principal and payment of interest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35257)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 18
  title Managements.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35257&sectionno=9&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Management.-- (1) The general superintendence, direction and management of affairs and`
  line `business of the Financial Corporation shall vest in a Board of directors which may exercise all powers and`
  line `do all such acts and things, as may be exercised or done by the Financial Corporation and are not by this`
  line `Act expressly directed or required to be done by the Financial Corporation in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall also be exercisable in`
  line `such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified by it, by the chairman, managing`
  line `director or the whole-time director.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35258)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 19
  title `Board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 7, for sections 5 to 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35258&sectionno=10&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Board of directors.--The Board of directors shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a director to be nominated as chairman under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(b) two directors nominated by the State Government of whom one director shall be a person who`
  line `has special knowledge of or experience in small-scale industries:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a Joint Financial Corporation, the number of directors shall be such as the`
  line `State Governments of the participating States may, by agreement among themselves, think fit to nominate`
  line `each participating State Government nominating not more than two directors:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a Joint Financial Corporation, the director, who shall have special`
  line `knowledge of, or experience in, small-scale industries, shall be nominated by that participating State`
  line `which, according to the terms of agreement between the participating States, is entitled to make such`
  line nomination;
  line
  line `(c) two directors nominated by the Small Industries Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) two directors nominated in the prescribed manner by the parties mentioned in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) such number of directors elected, in the prescribed manner, by share-holders, other than those`
  line `mentioned in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (3) of section 4, whose names are entered on the`
  line `register of shareholders of the Financial Corporation, ninety days before the date of the meeting in`
  line `which such election takes place on the following basis, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) where the total amount of issued equity share capital held by such shareholders is ten`
  line `per cent. or less of the total issued equity capital, two directors;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the total amount of issued equity share capital held by such shareholders is more`
  line `than ten per cent. but less than twenty-five per cent. of total issued equity capital, three directors;`
  line
  line `(iii) where the total amount of issued equity share capital held by such shareholders is`
  line `twenty-five per cent. or more of total issued equity capital, four directors; and`
  line
  line `(iv) where the total amount of issued equity share capital held by equity shareholders referred`
  line `to in this clause does not permit election of all the four directors, the Board shall co-opt such`
  line `number of directors as is required to make up the said number who shall retire in equal number on`
  line `the assumption of charge by the elected directors in the order of their co-option;`
  line
  line `(f) a managing director appointed in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the first constitution of the Board, the directors referred to in clause (d) shall be`
  line `nominated by the State Government and directors so nominated shall, for the purpose of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to be elected directors:`
  line
  line `Provided further that all the directors of the Board first constituted, other than the managing director,`
  line `shall retire at the end of the first year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (35320)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 20
  title `Omitted .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35320&sectionno=10A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `[Board of directors.] Omitted by the State Financial Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2000`
  line `(39 of 2000), s. 8 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35321)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title `Term of office and retirement of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 9, for sections 11 and 12 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35321&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Term of office and retirement of directors.--(1) A nominated director shall hold office during`
  line `the pleasure of the authority nominating him.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), a nominated director shall hold office for such term`
  line `not exceeding three years and shall also be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.`
  line
  line `(3) An elected director other than a director deemed to be elected under the first proviso to clause (d)`
  line `of section 10 shall hold office for three years and shall also be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35260)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disqualifications for being a director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 9, for sections 11 and 12 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35260&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Disqualifications for being a director.--No person shall be a director, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been found to be of unsound mind by a court of competent jurisdiction and the finding is`
  line `in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) is or at any time has been, adjudicated as insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts or`
  line `has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted by a court of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced in`
  line `respect thereof to imprisonment of not less than six months and a period of five years has not elapsed`
  line `from the date of expiry of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(d) is elected by the persons referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (3) of section 4 but not`
  line `registered as shareholder in his own right of unencumbered shares of a nominal value of not less than`
  line `ten thousand rupees in the Financial Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(e) has not paid any call in respect of shares of the Financial Corporation held by him, whether`
  line `alone or jointly with others, and six months have elapsed from the last day fixed for the payment of`
  line `the call.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35261)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 23
  title `Removal of director from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35261&sectionno=13&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The State Government may remove from office any`
  line `director who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has become, subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 12; or`
  line
  line `(b) without excuse sufficient in the opinion of the State Government to exonerate it, is absent`
  line `without leave of the Board from more than three consecutive meetings of the Board.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The shareholders, other than those mentioned in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4, whose names are entered on the register of shareholders, may, after giving to the director a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the manner as may be prescribed, by resolution passed by`
  line `majority of the votes of such shareholders holding in the aggregate not less than one-half of the total`
  line `issued equity share capital held by all such shareholders, remove any director elected under clause (d) of`
  line `section 10 and elect in his place another person to fill the vacancy so caused.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 13 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 10 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35262)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 24
  title `Resignation of office by director and filling up of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-section (1) and (1A) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35262&sectionno=14&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any director elected`
  line `under clause (d) of section 10 may, by giving notice in writing to the Chairman of the Board, resign from`
  line `his office and on such resignation being accepted, shall be deemed to have vacated his office.]`
  line
  line `(2) A casual vacancy in the office of an elected director shall be filled by election and a director so`
  line `elected shall hold office for the unexpired portion of the term of his predecessor.`
  line
  line `(3) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of`
  line `any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35263)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 25
  title `Chairman of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35263&sectionno=15&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Chairman of Board.--(1) The Small Industries Bank shall, in consultation with the State`
  line `Government nominate a director as a Chairman of the Board for such period not exceeding three years`
  line `and on such terms and conditions as the Small Industries Bank may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman shall not be a whole-time director unless he is also appointed to function`
  line `as the managing director:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chairman shall so long as he remains a director be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment as Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman shall preside over the meetings of the Board and the general meetings of the`
  line `Financial Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35264)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 26
  title `Remuneration of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 7, for section 16 (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35264&sectionno=16&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Remuneration of directors.--The directors other than the managing director and not being`
  line `servants of the Government shall be paid such fees as may be prescribed for attending meetings of the`
  line `Board and, if they are members of the Executive Committee, or any other committee appointed by the`
  line `Financial Corporation, for attending meetings of such committee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35265)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 27
  title `Managing director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35265&sectionno=17&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The managing director shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be appointed, in consultation with the Small Industries Bank, by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) be a whole-time officer of the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) perform such duties as the Board, by regulations, entrust or delegate to him;`
  line
  line `(d) hold office for such term not exceeding three years as the State Government may specify and`
  line `shall be eligible for re-appointment;`
  line
  line `(e) receive such salary and allowances and be subject to other terms and conditions of service as`
  line `the Board may, with the previous approval of the State Government, determine.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The State Government may, after consulting the Board, remove the managing director from`
  line `office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no managing director shall be so removed unless he has been given an opportunity of`
  line `showing cause against his removal.]`
  line
  line `^3 [(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government, with prior`
  line `consultation of the Small Industries Bank, shall have the right to terminate the term of office of the`
  line `managing director at any time, before the expiry of the term specified under clause (d) of sub-section (1)`
  line `by giving him notice of not less than three months in writing or three months salary and allowances in`
  line `lieu of such notice and the managing director shall also have right to relinquish his office at any time`
  line `before the expiry of term specified under clause (d) of sub-section (1) by giving to the State Government`
  line `notice of not less than three months in writing.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 13, for section 17 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 13 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35266)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 28
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for section 18 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35266&sectionno=18&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Executive Committee.--(1) The Board shall constitute an Executive Committee consisting of`
  line `the chairman and managing director, the whole-time directors and such other directors as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a Joint Financial Corporation, if the directors nominated under clause (b)`
  line `of section 10 represent different State Governments then, all of them shall be members of the Executive`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall discharge such functions as may be prescribed or as may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may constitute such other committees whether consisting wholly of directors or wholly`
  line `of, other persons of partly of directors and partly of other persons for such purpose or purposes as it may`
  line `think fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35267)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 29
  title `Meetings of the Board and Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35267&sectionno=19&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board and the Executive Committee`
  line `shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings as may be provided by regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All questions at a meeting shall be decided by a majority of votes of the members present, and in`
  line `the case of equality of votes, the Chairman or in his absence, any other person presiding, shall have a`
  line `second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(3) No director shall vote on any matter in which he is interested.`
  line
  line ^1[
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) If for any reason the Chairman of the Board or the Chairman of the Executive Committee is`
  line `unable to attend any meeting of the Board or, as the case may be, of the Executive Committee,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the meeting of the Board, a director ^3*** authorised by the Chairman of`
  line `the Board in writing shall preside at such meeting, but if the director so authorised is absent or if no`
  line `such authorisation has been made, the Board may elect a director to preside at the meeting; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of the meeting of the Executive Committee, a member authorised in writing by the`
  line `Chairman of that Committee shall preside at that meeting, but if the member so authorised is absent`
  line `or if no such authorisation has been made, the Committee may elect any of its members to preside at`
  line `that meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 9, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. The words ", not being the managing director" omitted by Act 43 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35268)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 30
  title `Powers of Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "shall be laid" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35268&sectionno=20&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such general or special directions as the Board`
  line `may from time to time give, the Executive Committee may deal with any matter within the competence of`
  line `the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The minutes of every meeting of the Executive Committee ^1[shall, after confirmation thereof at`
  line `the next meeting of the Executive Committee, be laid] before the Board at the next following meeting of`
  line `the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35269)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 31
  title `Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "one or more advisory committee or committees" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35269&sectionno=21&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Financial Corporation may appoint ^1[one or more committee or`
  line `committees consisting wholly of directors or wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of`
  line `other persons] for the purpose of assisting the Financial Corporation in the efficient discharge of its functions and, in particular, for the purpose of securing that those functions are exercised with due regard`
  line `to the circumstances and conditions prevailing in, and the requirements of, particular areas or industries.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35270)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 32
  title `Offices and agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 13, for section 22 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35270&sectionno=22&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Offices and agencies.--The Financial Corporation shall establish its head office and other`
  line `offices and agencies at such places as the State Government may, from time to time specify and save as`
  line `aforesaid, the Financial Corporation may establish additional offices or agencies in such other places`
  line `within the State as it may consider necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35271)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 33
  title `Officers and other employees of the Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 16 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35271&sectionno=23&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Financial Corporation may`
  line `appoint such officers, advisers and employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of its`
  line `functions, and determine, by regulations, their conditions of appointment and service and the`
  line `remuneration payable to them.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35272)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 34
  title `General duty of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35272&sectionno=24&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Board in discharging its functions under this Act shall act on`
  line `business principles due regard being had by it to the interests of industry, commerce and the general`
  line public.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35273)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 35
  title `Business which Financial Corporation may transact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35273&sectionno=25&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Business which Financial Corporation may transact.--^2[(1) The Financial Corporation may,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act, carry on and transact any of the following kinds of business,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) guaranteeing, on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon,`
  line
  line `(i) loans raised by industrial concerns which are repayable within a period not exceeding`
  line `twenty years, and are floated in the public market;`
  line
  line `(ii) loans raised by industrial concerns from scheduled banks or State cooperative banks ^3[or`
  line `other financial institutions];`
  line
  line `(b) guaranteeing, on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon, deferred payments due`
  line `from any industrial concern in connection with its purchase of capital goods within India;`
  line
  line `(c) underwriting of the issue of stock, shares, bonds or debentures by industrial concerns;`
  line
  line `(d) transferring for consideration any instruments relating to loans and advances granted by it to`
  line `industrial concerns;`
  line
  line `(e) acting as agent of the Central Government or the State Government or the Development Bank`
  line `or the Small Industries Bank or the IFCI Limited formed and registered under the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) or any other financial institution notified in this behalf by the Central Government in`
  line `respect of any matter connected with, or arising out of, the grant of loans or advances to an industrial`
  line `concern, or subscription to debentures of an industrial concern or relating to the business of the`
  line `Development Bank, Small Industries Bank, IFCI Limited or financial institution;`
  line
  line `(f) subscribing to, or purchasing of, the stock, shares, bonds or debentures of an industrial concern`
  line `or any other concern;`
  line
  line `(g) retaining as part of its assets any stock, shares, bonds or debentures which it may acquire by`
  line `subscription or in fulfilment of its underwriting liabilities and disposing of the stock, shares, bonds or`
  line `debentures so acquired;`
  line
  line `(h) granting loans or advances to, or subscribing to debentures of, an industrial concern,`
  line `repayable within a period not exceeding twenty years from the date on which they are granted or`
  line `subscribed to, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Financial Corporation may, with the prior approval of the Small Industries Bank,`
  line `exceed the said limit of twenty years up to a further period of ten years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to preclude the Financial`
  line `Corporation from granting loans or advances to, or subscribing to debentures of, and industrial concern to which may be attached an option to convert such debentures or loans into stock or shares of the industrial`
  line `concern:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Financial Corporation may, in the exercise of such option, convert the amounts`
  line `outstanding on such debentures or loans into stock or shares of the industrial concern if such concern`
  line `increases its subscribed capital by the issue of further stock or shares in accordance with and subject to,`
  line `the provisions of Section 81 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, the expression "the amounts outstanding on such debentures or loans"`
  line `shall mean the principal, interest and other charges payable on such debentures or loans as at the time`
  line `when the amounts are sought to be converted into stock or shares;`
  line
  line `(i) accepting or discounting promissory notes and bills of exchange made, down, accepted or`
  line `endorsed by industrial concerns or by any person selling capital goods manufactured by one industrial`
  line `concern to another industrial concern;`
  line
  line `(j) undertaking research and surveys for evaluating or dealing with marketing or investments or`
  line `undertaking and carrying on techno-economic studies or other activities in connection with the`
  line `development of any industry;`
  line
  line `(k) providing technical and administrative assistance to any industrial concern or any person for`
  line `the promotion, management or expansion of any industry;`
  line
  line `(l) planning and assisting in the promotion and development of industries;`
  line
  line `(m) providing consultancy and merchant banking services;`
  line
  line `(n) acting as the trustee for the holders of debentures or other securities;`
  line
  line `(o) leasing, sub-leasing or giving on hire or hire-purchase of industrial plant, equipment,`
  line `machinery or any other asset;`
  line
  line `(p) factoring;`
  line
  line `(q) providing export related credit and services;`
  line
  line `(r) undertaking money market related activities;`
  line
  line `(s) setting up of mutual funds and undertaking asset management activity;`
  line
  line `(t) promoting, forming or conducting or assisting in the promotion, formation, or conduct of`
  line `companies, subsidiaries, societies, trusts or such other associations of persons as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(u) opening or confirming or endorsing letters of credit and negotiating or collecting bills and`
  line `other documents drawn thereunder;`
  line
  line `(v) doing such other business as the Small Industries Bank may authorise, and or generally the`
  line `doing of such acts and things as may be incidental to or consequential upon, the exercise of its powers`
  line `or the discharge of its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Corporation may receive, in consideration of any of the services mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1), such commission, brokerage, interest, remuneration or fee as may be agreed upon.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5) of section 7, the aggregate of contingent liabilities of`
  line `the Financial Corporation under clauses (a), (b)`
  line `^5[(c) and (ca)] of sub-section (1) shall not at any time`
  line `exceed twice the paid-up share capital and reserve fund of the Corporation except with the prior approval`
  line `of the State Government and in consultation with the ^6[Small Industries Bank] but in no case shall exceed`
  line `thrice the paid-up share capital and reserve fund of the Corporation.]`
  line
  line `^7[(4) Nothing contained in this section shall entitle any Financial Corporation to hold shares in any`
  line `company, whether as pledgee, mortgagee or absolute owner, of an amount exceeding thirty per cent. of`
  line `the subscribed share capital of that company or thirty per cent. of its own paid-up share capital and free`
  line `reserves, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(5) If, on the commencement of the State Financial Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1972`
  line `(77 of 1972), any Financial Corporation is holding shares in excess of the limits specified in`
  line `sub-section (4), the Corporation shall report the matter forthwith to the Reserve Bank and shall, within`
  line `such period as the Reserve Bank may allow, so reduce its share holding as to conform to the provisions of`
  line `that sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 10, for section 25 (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 15 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 43 of 1985, s. 15 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 15, for "and (c)" (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 17, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 15 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (35274)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to acquire rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 16 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35274&sectionno=25A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Power to acquire rights.--The Financial Corporation shall have the right to acquire, by`
  line `transfer or assignment, the rights and interests of any such financial institution as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government (including any other rights incidental thereto) in relation to any loan or advance`
  line `granted or any amount recoverable by such institution, either in whole or in part, by the execution or issue`
  line `of any instrument or by the transfer of any instrument by endorsement or in any other manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that such loan or advance or amount relates to any business which the Financial Corporation`
  line `may transact under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_b:
  sectionId (35275)
  sectionNo 25B
  orderNo 37
  title `Gifts, grants, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 18 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35275&sectionno=25B&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[25B. Gifts, grants, etc.--The Financial Corporation may receive gifts, grants, donations or`
  line `benefactions from Government or any other source.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35276)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 38
  title `Limit of accommodation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35276&sectionno=26&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Limit of accommodation.--On and from the commencement of the State Financial`
  line `Corporations (Amendment) Act, 2000 (39 of 2000), the Financial Corporation shall not enter into any`
  line `arrangements under clause (a), (d) or (h) of sub-section (1) of section 25 with any industrial concern so`
  line `that the total amount outstanding against that concern in respect of all such arrangements together with`
  line `the amount of the face value of the shares and stocks of that concern whether subscribed or agreed to be`
  line `subscribed and the outstanding liabilities on account of underwriting agreements and the deferred`
  line `payments guarantees is more than--`
  line
  line `(i) five hundred lakhs of rupees in the case of a corporation established by or under any other law`
  line `or a company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or a co-operative`
  line `society registered under the Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912) or any other law relating to`
  line `co-operative societies for the time being in force; and`
  line
  line `(ii) two hundred lakhs of rupees in any other case:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Financial Corporation may, with the prior approval of the Small Industries Bank,`
  line `exceed the limit under clause (i) or clause (ii) up to four times.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35277)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to impose conditions for accommodation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 17, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35277&sectionno=27&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) In entering into any arrangement under`
  line `section 25 with an industrial concern, the Financial Corporation may impose such conditions as it may`
  line `think necessary or expedient for protecting the interests of the Financial Corporation and securing that the`
  line `accommodation granted by it is put to the best use by the industrial concern.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Where any arrangement entered into by the Financial Corporation with an industrial concern`
  line `provides for the appointment by the Financial Corporation of one or more directors of such industrial`
  line `concern, such provision and any appointment of directors made in pursuance thereof shall be valid and`
  line `effective notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum, articles of association or any other`
  line `instrument relating to the industrial concern, and any provision regarding share qualification, age limit,`
  line `number of directorships, removal of office of directors and such like conditions contained in any such law`
  line `or instrument aforesaid shall not apply to any director appointed by the Financial Corporation in`
  line `pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Any director appointed in pursuance of sub-section (2) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the Financial Corporation and may be removed or`
  line `substituted by any person by order in writing by the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35278)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 40
  title `Prohibited business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35278&sectionno=28&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Financial Corporation shall not--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) except as provided in section 8, accept deposits;`
  line
  line `(b) except as provided in clauses ^3[(da)], (f) and (g) of sub-section (1) of section 25, subscribe to`
  line `the shares or stock of any company;]`
  line
  line `(c) grant any loan or advance on the security of its own shares;`
  line
  line `^4[(d) grant any form of assistance to any industrial concern in respect of which the aggregate of`
  line `the paid-up share capital and free reserves exceeds ten crores of rupees or such higher amount not`
  line `exceeding thirty crores of rupees as the State Government, on the recommendation of the Small`
  line `Industries Bank, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) The Financial Corporation shall not enter into any kind of business with any industrial concern,`
  line `of which any of the directors of the Financial Corporation is a proprietor, partner, director, manager,`
  line `agent, employee or guarantor, or in which one or more directors of the Financial Corporation together`
  line `hold substantial interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply to any industrial concern if any director of the Financial`
  line Corporation--
  line
  line `(i) is nominated as a director of the Board of such concern by the Government or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or by a Corporation`
  line `established by or under any other law; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is elected on the Board of such concern by virtue of shares held in the concern by Government`
  line `or a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or by a`
  line `Corporation established by or under any other law, by reason only of such nomination or election, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Substantial interest" in relation to an industrial concern means the beneficial interest`
  line `held by one or more of the directors of the Financial Corporation or by any relative [as defined in clause`
  line `(41) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)] of such director whether singly or taken`
  line `together, in the shares of the industrial concern, the aggregate amount paid-up on which either exceeds`
  line `five lakhs of rupees or five per cent. of the paid-up share capital of the industrial concern, whichever is`
  line less.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(i) shall not apply to any transaction relating to the business entered into prior to the`
  line `commencement of the State Financial Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1972 (77 of 1972) and all such`
  line `business and any transaction in relation thereto may be implemented or continued as if that Act had`
  line `not come into force;`
  line
  line `(ii) shall apply only so long as the conditions precedent to such disability as set out in`
  line `sub-section continue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section 28 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 77 of 1972, s. 18 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 13, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 18 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 20, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 18 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35279)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 41
  title `Rights of Financial Corporation in case of default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35279&sectionno=29&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any industrial concern, which is`
  line `under a liability to the Financial Corporation under an agreement, makes any default in repayment of any`
  line `loan or advance or any instalment thereof ^1[or in meeting its obligations in relation to any guarantee given`
  line `by the Corporation] or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of its agreement with the Financial`
  line `Corporation, the Financial Corporation shall have the ^2[right to take over the management or possession`
  line `or both of the industrial concerns], as well as the ^3[right to transfer by way of lease or sale] and realise the`
  line `property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any transfer of property made by the Financial Corporation, in exercise of its powers ^4*** under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall vest in the transferee all rights in or to the property transferred ^5[as if the transfer]`
  line `had been made by the owner of the property.`
  line
  line `(3) The Financial Corporation shall have the same rights and powers with respect to goods`
  line `manufactured or produced wholly or partly from goods forming part of the security held by it as it had`
  line `with respect to the original goods.`
  line
  line `^6[(4)`
  line `^7[Where any action has been taken against an industrial concern] under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), all costs, ^8[charges and expenses which in the opinion of the Financial Corporation have`
  line `been properly incurred] by it ^9[as incidental thereto] shall be recoverable from the industrial concern and`
  line `the money which is received by it`
  line `^10*** shall, in the absence of any contract to the contrary, be held by it`
  line `in trust to be applied firstly, in payment of such costs, charges and expenses and, secondly, in discharge of`
  line `the debt due to the Financial Corporation, and the residue of the money so received shall be paid to the`
  line `person entitled thereto.]`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line `^7[Where the Financial Corporation has taken any action against an industrial concern] under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), the Financial Corporation shall be deemed to be the owner of such concern,`
  line `for the purposes of suits by or against the concern, and shall sue and be sued in the name of ^11[the`
  line concern].
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 19 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "right to take over the management of the industrial concern" (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 14, for "right to sell" (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `4. The words "of sale and relaisation" omitted by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `5 Subs. by s.14, ibid., for "as if the sale"(w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 19, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1956).`
  line
  line `8 Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 14, for "charges and expenses properly incurred" (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `9 Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 19, for "as incidental to such management, or transfer and realization." (w.e.f. 30-12-1956).`
  line
  line `10. The words "from such management, or transfer and realization" omitted by s.19, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `11 Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 14, for "the owner for the concern" (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35280)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35280&sectionno=30&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any`
  line `agreement to the contrary, the Financial Corporation may, by notice in writing, require any industrial`
  line `concern to which it has granted any loan or advance to discharge forthwith in full its liabilities to the`
  line `Financial Corporation,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Board that false or misleading information in any material particular was`
  line `given by the industrial concern in its application for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the industrial concern has failed to comply with the terms of its contract with the Financial`
  line `Corporation in the matter of the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the industrial concern is unable to pay its debts or`
  line `that proceedings for liquidation may be commenced in respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the Financial Corporation as`
  line `security for the loan or advance is not insured and kept insured by the industrial concern to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Financial Corporation or depreciates in value to such an extent that, in the opinion of the Board, further security to the satisfaction of the Board should be given and such security is not`
  line `given; or`
  line
  line `(e) if, without the permission of the Board, any machinery, plant or other equipment, whether`
  line `forming part of the security or otherwise, is removed from the premises of the industrial concern`
  line `without being replaced; or`
  line
  line `(f) if for any reason it is necessary to protect the interests of the Financial Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35281)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 43
  title `Special provisions for enforcement of claims by Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35281&sectionno=31&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an`
  line `industrial concern, in breach of any agreement, makes any default in repayment of any loan or advance or`
  line `any instalment thereof ^1[or in meeting its obligations in relation to any guarantee given by the`
  line `Corporation] or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of its agreement with the Financial Corporation`
  line `or where the Financial Corporation requires an industrial concern to make immediate repayment of any`
  line `loan or advance under section 30 and the industrial concern fails to make such repayment, ^2[then, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of section 29 of this Act and of section 69 of the Transfer of Property Act,`
  line `1882 (4 of 1882)] any officer of the Financial Corporation, generally or specially authorised by the Board`
  line `in this behalf, may apply to the district judge within the limits of whose jurisdiction the industrial concern`
  line `carries on the whole or a substantial part of its business for one or more of the following reliefs,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for an order for the sale of the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the`
  line `^3[Financial Corporation] as security for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `^4[(aa) for enforcing the liability of any surety; or]`
  line
  line `(b) for transferring the management of the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(c) for an ad interim injunction restraining the industrial concern from transferring or removing its`
  line `machinery or plant or equipment from the premises of the industrial concern without the permission`
  line `of the Board, where such removal is apprehended.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall state the nature and extent of the liability of the`
  line `industrial concern to the Financial Corporation, the ground on which it is made and such other particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 20 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 19 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35282)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 44
  title `Procedure of district judge in respect of applications under section 31.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35282&sectionno=32&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the`
  line `application is for the reliefs mentioned in clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (1) of section 31, the district`
  line `judge shall pass an ad interim order attaching the security, or so much of the property of the industrial`
  line `concern as would on being sold realise in his estimate an amount equivalent in value to the outstanding`
  line `liability of the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation, together with the costs of the proceedings`
  line `taken under section 31, with or without an ad interim injunction restraining the industrial concern from`
  line `transferring or removing its machinery, plant or equipment.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) When the application is for the relief mentioned in clause (aa) of sub-section (1) of section 31,`
  line `the district judge shall issue a notice calling upon the surety to show cause on a date to be specified in the`
  line `notice why his liability should not be enforced.]`
  line
  line `(2) When the application is for the relief mentioned in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 31, the`
  line `district judge shall grant an ad interim injunction restraining the industrial concern from transferring or`
  line `removing its machinery, plant or equipment and issue a notice calling upon the industrial concern to show`
  line `cause, on a date to be specified in the notice, why the management of the industrial concern should not be`
  line `transferred to the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) Before passing any order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2)`
  line `^2[, or issuing a notice under`
  line `sub-section (1A),] the district judge may, if he thinks fit, examine the officer making the application.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) At the same time as he passes an order under sub-section (1), the district judge shall issue to the`
  line `industrial concern or to the owner of the security attached a notice accompanied by copies of the order,`
  line `the application and the evidence, if any, recorded by him calling upon it or him to show cause on a date to`
  line `be specified in the notice why the ad interim order of attachment should not be made absolute or the`
  line `injunction confirmed.`
  line
  line `(4A) If no cause is shown on or before the date specified in the notice under sub-section (1A) the`
  line `district judge shall forthwith order the enforcement of the liability of the surety.]`
  line
  line `(5) If no cause is shown on or before the date specified in the notice under sub-sections (2) and (4),`
  line `the district Judge shall forthwith make the ad interim order absolute and direct the sale of the attached`
  line `property or transfer the management of the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation or confirm the`
  line injunction.
  line
  line `(6) If cause is shown, the district judge shall proceed to investigate the claim of the Financial`
  line `Corporation in accordance with the provisions contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908)`
  line `insofar as such provisions may be applied thereto.`
  line
  line `(7) After making an investigation under sub-section (6), the district judge may--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm the order of attachment and direct the sale of the attached property;`
  line
  line `(b) vary the order of attachment so as to release a portion of the property from attachment and`
  line `direct the sale of the remainder of the attached property;`
  line
  line `(c) release the property from attachment;`
  line
  line `(d) confirm or dissolve the injunction; ^4***;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) direct the enforcement of the liability of the surety or reject the claim made in this behalf;`
  line or]
  line
  line `(e) transfer the management of the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation or reject the`
  line `claim made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that when making an order under clause (c)`
  line `^2[or making an order rejecting the claim to`
  line `enforce the liability of the surety under clause (da) or making an order rejecting the claim to transfer the`
  line `management of the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation under clause (e)], the district judge`
  line `may make such further orders as he thinks necessary to protect the interests of the Financial Corporation`
  line `and may apportion the costs of the proceedings in such manner as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that unless the Financial Corporation intimates to the district judge that it will not`
  line `appeal against any order releasing any property from attachment ^2[or rejecting the claim to enforce the`
  line `liability of the surety or rejecting the claim to transfer the industrial concern to the Financial Corporation],`
  line `such order shall not be given effect to, until the expiry of the period fixed under sub-section (9) within`
  line `which an appeal may be preferred or, if an appeal is preferred, unless the High Court otherwise directs`
  line `until the appeal is disposed of.`
  line
  line `(8) An order of attachment or sale of property under this section shall be carried into effect as far as`
  line `practicable in the manner provided in the Code of Civil Procedure 1908 (5 of 1908) for the attachment or`
  line `sale of property in execution of a decree as if the Financial Corporation were the decree-holder.`
  line
  line `^5[(8A) An order under this section transferring the management of an industrial concern to the`
  line `Financial Corporation shall be carried into effect, as far as may be practicable, in the manner provided in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the possession of immovable property or the delivery of`
  line `movable property in execution of a degree, as if the Financial Corporation were the decree-holder.]`
  line
  line `(9) Any party aggrieved by an order ^6[under sub-section (4A), sub-section (5)] or sub-section (7) may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date of the order, appeal to the High Court, and upon such appeal the High`
  line `Court may, after hearing the parties, pass such orders thereon as it thinks proper.`
  line
  line `(10) Where proceedings for liquidation in respect of an industrial concern have commenced before an`
  line `application is made under sub-section (1) of section 31, nothing in this section shall be construed as`
  line `giving to the Financial Corporation any preference over the other creditors of the industrial concern not`
  line `conferred on it by any other law.`
  line
  line `^7[(11) The functions of a district judge under this section shall be exercisable--`
  line
  line `(a) in a presidency town, where there is a city civil court having jurisdiction, by a judge of that`
  line `court and in the absence of such court, by the High Court; and`
  line
  line `(b) elsewhere, also by an additional district judge ^8[or by any judge of the principal court of civil`
  line jurisdiction].]
  line
  line `^8[(12) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that any court competent to grant an ad interim`
  line `injunction under this section shall also have the power to appoint a Receiver and to exercise all the other`
  line `powers incidental thereto.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 20 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `4. The word "or" omitted by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 20, for "under sub-section (5)" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 15 for sub-section (11) (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 21 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (35322)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Financial Corporation to appoint directors or administrators of an industrial concern when management is taken over.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35322&sectionno=32A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Power of Financial Corporation to appoint directors or administrators of an industrial`
  line `concern when management is taken over.--(1) When the management of an industrial concern is taken`
  line `over by the Financial Corporation, the Financial Corporation may, by order notified in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint as many persons as it thinks fit,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which the industrial concern is a company as defined in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) to be directors of that industrial concern; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, to be administrators of that industrial concern.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to appoint directors or administrators under this section includes the power to appoint`
  line `any individual, firm or company to be the managing agent or manager of the industrial concern on such`
  line `terms and conditions as the Financial Corporation may think fit.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Nothing in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or in any other law for the time being in force`
  line `or in any instrument relating to the industrial concern shall, insofar as it makes in relation to a director,`
  line `any provision for the holding of any share qualification, age limit, restriction on the number of`
  line `directorships, retirement by rotation or removal from office, apply to any director appointed by the`
  line `Financial Corporation under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 16 (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (35284)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 46
  title `Effect of notified order under section 32A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35284&sectionno=32B&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Effect of notified order under section 32A.-- On the issue of a notified order under`
  line `section 32AOn the issue of a notified order under`
  line `section 32A.--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which the industrial concern is a company as defined in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) all persons holding office as directors of the industrial concern and in any other`
  line `case, all persons holding any office having the powers of superintendence, direction and control of the`
  line `industrial concern, immediately before the issue of the notified order, shall be deemed to have vacated`
  line `their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) any contract of management between the industrial concern and any managing agent or any`
  line `director or manager there of holding office as such immediately before the issue of the notified order`
  line `shall be deemed to have terminated;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an industrial concern which is a company as defined in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) the managing agent, if any, appointed under section 32A shall be deemed to have`
  line `been duly appointed in pursuance of the said Act and the memorandum and articles of association of`
  line `the industrial concern and the provisions of the said Act and the memorandum and articles shall,`
  line `subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, apply accordingly, but no such managing agent`
  line `shall be removed from office except with the previous consent of the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) the directors or the administrators appointed under section 32A shall take such steps as may`
  line `be necessary to take into their custody or under their control all the property, effects and actionable`
  line `claims to which the industrial concern is, or appears to be, entitled, and all the property and effects of`
  line `the industrial concern shall be deemed to be in the custody of the directors or administrators, as the`
  line `case may be, as from the date of the notified order;`
  line
  line `(e) the directors appointed under section 32A shall, for all purposes, be the directors of the`
  line `industrial concern duly constituted under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and such directors, or`
  line `as the case may be, the administrators appointed under section 32A, shall alone be entitled to exercise`
  line `all the powers of the directors or as the case may be, of the persons exercising powers of`
  line `superintendence, direction and control, of the industrial concern, whether such powers are derived`
  line `from the said Act or from the memorandum or articles of association of the industrial concern or from`
  line `any other source whatsoever.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_c:
  sectionId (35285)
  sectionNo 32C
  orderNo 47
  title `Powers and duties of directors and administrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35285&sectionno=32C&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[32C. Powers and duties of directors and administrators.-- (1) Subject to the control of the`
  line `Financial Corporation, the directors, or as the case may be, the administrators appointed under section`
  line `32A, shall take such steps as may be necessary for the purpose of efficiently managing the business of the`
  line `industrial concern and shall exercise such powers and have such duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers vested in them under sub-section (1), the`
  line `directors or as the case may be, the administrators appointed under section 32A, may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Financial Corporation, make an application to a court for the purpose of cancelling or`
  line `varying any contract or agreement entered into any time before the issue of the notified order under`
  line `section 32A, between the industrial concern and any other person and the court may, if satisfied after due`
  line `inquiry that such contract or agreement had been entered into in bad faith and is detrimental to the`
  line `interests of the industrial concern, make an order cancelling or varying (either unconditionally or subject`
  line `to such conditions as it may think fit to impose) that contract or agreement and the contract or agreement`
  line `shall have effect accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_d:
  sectionId (35286)
  sectionNo 32D
  orderNo 48
  title `No right to compensation for termination of contract of managing agent, managing director, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35286&sectionno=32D&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[32D. No right to compensation for termination of contract of managing agent, managing`
  line `director, etc.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any contract or in any law for`
  line `the time being in force, no managing agent, managing director or any other director or a manager or any`
  line `person in charge of management of an industrial concern shall be entitled to any compensation for the`
  line `loss of office or for the premature termination under this Act of any contract of management entered into`
  line `by him with such concern.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any such managing agent or`
  line `managing director, or any other director or manager or any such person in charge of management to`
  line `recover from the industrial concern, moneys recoverable otherwise than by way of such compensation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_e:
  sectionId (35287)
  sectionNo 32E
  orderNo 49
  title `Application of Act 1 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35287&sectionno=32E&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[32E. Application of Act 1 of 1956.-- (1) Where the management of an industrial concern, being a`
  line `company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), is taken over by the Financial Corporation,`
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in the said Act or in the memorandum or articles of association`
  line `of such concern,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall not be lawful for the shareholders of such concern or any other person to nominate or`
  line `appoint any person to be a director of the concern;`
  line
  line `(b) no resolution passed at any meeting of the shareholders of such concern shall be given effect`
  line `to unless approved by the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) no proceeding for the winding up of such concern or for the appointment of receiver in respect`
  line `thereof shall lie in any court, except with the consent of the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (1) and to the other provisions contained in this`
  line `Act and subject to such other exceptions, restrictions and limitations, if any, as the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,`
  line `the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) shall continue to apply to such concern in the same manner as it`
  line `applied thereto before the issue of the notified order under section 32A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_f:
  sectionId (35323)
  sectionNo 32F
  orderNo 50
  title `Restriction on tiling of suite for dissolution, etc., of an industrial concern not being a company when its management is taken over.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35323&sectionno=32F&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[32F. Restriction on filing of suite for dissolution, etc., of an industrial concern not being a`
  line `company when its management is taken over.-- (1) Where the management of an industrial concern`
  line `not being a company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) is taken over by the Financial`
  line `Corporation, no suit or proceedings for dissolution or for partition shall, insofar as it relates to that`
  line `industrial concern, lie in any court or before any tribunal or other authority except with the consent of the`
  line `Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) No proceeding for the appointment of any official assignee or receiver in relation to any industrial`
  line `concern the management of which has been taken over by the Financial Corporation shall lie in any court`
  line `except with consent of the Financial Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_g:
  sectionId (35289)
  sectionNo 32G
  orderNo 51
  title `Recovery of amounts due to the Financial Corporation as an arrear of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 21 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35289&sectionno=32G&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_32_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[32G. Recovery of amounts due to the Financial Corporation as an arrear of land`
  line `revenue.--Where any amount is due to the Financial Corporation in respect of any accommodation`
  line `granted by it to any industrial concern, the Financial Corporation or any person authorised by it in writing`
  line `in this behalf, may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery, make an application to the State`
  line `Government for the recovery of the amount due to it, and if the State Government or such authority, as`
  line `that Government may specify in this behalf, is satisfied, after following such procedure as may be`
  line `prescribed, that any amount is so due, it may issue a certificate for that amount to the Collector, and the`
  line `Collector shall proceed to recover that amount in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (35290)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 52
  title `Funds of the Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35290&sectionno=33&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Financial Corporation shall have its own fund,`
  line `and all receipts of the Financial Corporation shall be carried thereto and all payments by the Corporation`
  line `shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the fund shall be deposited in the Reserve Bank ^2[or the State Bank of`
  line `India or a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959`
  line `(38 of 1959)] ^3[or in any of the banks specified in column 2 of the First Schedule to the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) ^1[or any of the banks`
  line `specified in column 2 of the First Schedule to the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980)] ^4[or, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, in a scheduled bank or`
  line `a State Co-operative Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 21 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 17, for "or with any agency of the Reserve Bank other than a Government treasury"`
  line `(w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 22 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 18, for "or in a scheduled bank in consultation with the Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (35291)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 53
  title `Investment of funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 21, for section 34 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35291&sectionno=34&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Investment of funds.--The Financial Corporation may invest its funds in accordance with`
  line `applicable guidelines and prudential norms as may be prescribed and in such securities as the Board may`
  line `decide from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (35292)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 54
  title `Disposal of profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35292&sectionno=35&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Corporation shall establish a reserve fund.`
  line
  line `(2) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets and all other matters`
  line `which are usually provided for by banking companies, the Financial Corporation may out of its net annual`
  line `profits declare a dividend;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line ^2*****
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso omitted by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 22 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (35293)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 55
  title `Special reserve fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for section 35A (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35293&sectionno=35A&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[35A. Special reserve fund.--(1) the Financial Corporation may establish a special reserve fund, to`
  line `which shall be transferred such portion of the dividends accruing to the State Government Development`
  line `Bank and the Small Industries Bank on the shares of the Financial Corporation as may be fixed by`
  line `agreement between the State Government, Development Bank and the Small Industries Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that after the notified date this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words "the State`
  line `Government, the Development Bank and the Small Industries Bank", the words "the State Government`
  line `and the Small Industries Bank" have been substituted except as regards all dividends accruing in respect`
  line `of any completed accounting period prior to the notified date.`
  line
  line `(2) No shareholder of the Financial Corporation, other than the State Government or the Small`
  line `Industries Bank, shall have any claim to the special reserve fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount standing to the credit of the special reserve fund may be utilised by the Financial`
  line `Corporation for only such purposes as are approved by the State Government and the Small Industries`
  line Bank.]
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (35294)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 56
  title `General meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35294&sectionno=36&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) A general meeting (hereinafter referred to as the annual general meeting)`
  line `shall be held annually at a place in the State where there is an office of the Financial Corporation within`
  line `^1[four months] from the date on which the annual accounts of the Financial Corporation are closed, and a`
  line `general meeting may be convened by the Board at any other time.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The shareholders present at the annual general meeting shall be entitled to discuss and adopt--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance-sheet and profit and loss account of the Financial Corporation made up to the date`
  line `on which its accounts are closed and balanced;`
  line
  line `(b) the report of working of the Financial Corporation for the period covered by the accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) the auditor's report on the balance-sheet and accounts; and`
  line
  line `(d) proposals for declaration of dividend and capitalisation of reserves.`
  line
  line `(3) The shareholders present at an annual general meeting may also discuss any other matter to be`
  line `transacted at such meetings in accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 24, for "three months" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 24, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (35295)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 57
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35295&sectionno=37&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The accounts of the Financial Corporation shall be audited by auditors duly`
  line `qualified to act as the auditors under sub-section (1) of section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), who shall be appointed by the Financial Corporation in general meeting of shareholders out`
  line `of the panel of auditors approved by the Reserve Bank of India for such terms and on such remuneration`
  line `as the Reserve Bank may fix.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet of the Financial`
  line `Corporation, and it shall be his duty to examine it, together with the accounts and vouchers relating`
  line `thereto, and every auditor shall have a list delivered to him of all books kept by the Financial Corporation`
  line `and shall at all reasonable times have access to the books, accounts and other documents of the Financial`
  line `Corporation and may in relation to such accounts examine any director or officer of the Financial`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(3) The auditors shall make a report to the shareholders upon the annual balance-sheet and accounts,`
  line `and in every such report they shall state whether in their opinion the balance-sheet is a full and fair`
  line `balance-sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to exhibit a true and`
  line `correct view of the state of affairs of the Financial Corporation, and in case they had called for any`
  line `explanation or information from the Board, whether it has been given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, at`
  line `any time issue directions to the auditors requiring them to report to it upon the adequacy of measures`
  line `taken by the Financial Corporation for the protection of its shareholders and creditors or upon the`
  line `sufficiency of their procedure in auditing the affairs of the Financial Corporation and may enlarge or`
  line `extend the scope of the audit or direct that a different procedure in audit be adopted, or direct that any`
  line `other examination be made by the auditors, if in its opinion public interest so requires.`
  line
  line `(5) The Financial Corporation shall send a copy of every report of the auditors to the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India at least one month before it is placed before the shareholders.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the preceding sub-sections, the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India may, either of his own motion or on a request received in this behalf from a State`
  line `Government, undertake such audit and at such times as he may consider necessary:`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(7) Every audit report under sub-section (6) shall be forwarded to the State Government and the`
  line `Government shall cause the same to be laid before the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 25 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (35296)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 58
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35296&sectionno=37A&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Small Industries Bank] at any time may, with the approval of the`
  line `Central Government, and on being directed so to do by that Government shall cause an inspection to be`
  line `made by one or more of its officers of the working of any Financial Corporation and its books and`
  line `accounts; and the ^1[Small Industries Bank] shall send the report of such inspection to the Central`
  line `Government and to the State Government and shall supply a copy thereof to the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every director or every officer of the Financial Corporation to produce to`
  line `any officer making an inspection under sub-section (1) all such books, accounts and other documents in`
  line `his custody or power and to furnish him with any statement and information relating to the affairs of the`
  line `Financial Corporation as the said officer may require of him within such time as the said officer may`
  line specify.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, no court, tribunal or other authority shall have power to require`
  line `the ^1[Small Industries Bank] or any of its officers to produce before such court, tribunal or other authority`
  line `the report of the inspection made by it under sub-section (1) or any copy thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, after considering any report sent to it under sub-section (1), give such`
  line `instructions to the Board as it considers necessary and it shall be the duty of the Board to comply with`
  line `such instructions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (35297)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 59
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35297&sectionno=38&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Financial Corporation shall furnish to the State Government, the ^2[Small`
  line `Industries Bank] and the Reserve Bank such statements and returns in such form as the State Government,`
  line `the ^2[Small Industries Bank] or the Reserve Bank may require from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Corporation shall furnish ^3[to the State Government, the ^2[Small Industries Bank]`
  line `and the Reserve Bank] within ^4[four months] of the close of each financial year a statement in the`
  line `prescribed form of its assets and liabilities as at the close of that year, together with a profit and loss`
  line `account for the year, the auditors' report and a report of the working of the Financial Corporation during`
  line `the year and copies of the said statement, account and reports shall be published in the Official Gazette`
  line `and shall also be laid before the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 25, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 27, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 38, for "to the State Government and to the Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 22, for "three months" (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (35298)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power to give instructions to Financial Corporation on questions of policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35298&sectionno=39&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the`
  line `discharge of its functions, the Board shall be guided by such instructions on questions of policy as may be`
  line `given to it by the State Government ^1[in consultation with ^2[and after obtaining the advice of,] the ^3[Small`
  line `Industries Bank]].`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the State Government and the Board as to whether a question is or is`
  line `not a question of policy, the decision of the State Government shall be final.`
  line
  line `^4[(2A) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) shall apply in a case where a State`
  line `Government holds less than fifty-one per cent. of the equity shares in the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2B) Notwithstanding the equity share holding of a Financial Corporation by a State Government, the`
  line `State Government may advise the Financial Corporations on the matters of policy.]`
  line
  line `(3) If the Board fails to carry out the instructions on the question of policy laid down by the State`
  line `Government ^5[under sub-section (1) of this section or the instructions given to the Board under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 37A], the State Government shall have the power to supersede the Board and`
  line `appoint a new Board in its place to function until a properly constituted Board is set up, and the decision`
  line `of the State Government as to the grounds for superseding the Board shall not be questioned in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 23 (w.e.f.1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Inserted by Act 77 of 1972, s. 26 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 28, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 23, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (35299)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 61
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35299&sectionno=40&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Financial Corporation shall not, except as`
  line `otherwise required by this Act or any other law for the time being in force, divulge any information`
  line `relating to, or to the affairs of, its constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in accordance with`
  line `the law or practice and usage, customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the Financial`
  line `Corporation to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Corporation may, for the purpose of efficient discharge of its functions under this`
  line `Act, collect from, or furnish to--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955`
  line `(23 of 1955), any subsidiary bank within the meaning of the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks)`
  line `Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), any corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or under section 3 of`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), any`
  line `other scheduled bank, any ^2[State Co-operative Bank, the Small Industries Bank or the Development`
  line Bank],
  line
  line `such credit information or other information as it may consider useful for the purpose, in such manner and`
  line `at such time as it may think fit,`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "credit information" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as in clause (c) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), subject`
  line `to the modification that the banking company referred to therein shall mean a bank referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3)] Every director, auditor, officer or other employee of the Financial Corporation shall, before`
  line `entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 1983, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-12-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 29, for "State co-operative Bank or the Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Section 40 re-numbered as sub-section (3) thereof by Act 48 of 1983, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-12-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (35300)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 62
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35300&sectionno=41&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director shall be indemnified by the Financial Corporation`
  line `against all losses and expenses incurred by him in the discharge of his duties except such as are caused by`
  line `his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director shall not be responsible for any other director or for any officer or other employee of`
  line `the Financial Corporation or for any loss or expenses resulting to the Financial Corporation by the`
  line `insufficiency or deficiency of value of or title to any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of`
  line `the Financial Corporation or by the wrongful act of any person under obligation to the Financial`
  line `Corporation or by anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office or in relation`
  line thereto.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41_a:
  sectionId (35301)
  sectionNo 41A
  orderNo 63
  title `Protection of action taken by persons appointed under section 27 or section 32A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 21 (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35301&sectionno=41A&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[41A. Protection of action taken by persons appointed under section 27 or section 32A.-- No`
  line `suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against any person appointed as director,`
  line `administrator, managing agent or manager by the Financial Corporation in pursuance of Section 27 or`
  line `section 32A for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done by him as such director,`
  line `administrator, managing agent or manager.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41_b:
  sectionId (35302)
  sectionNo 41B
  orderNo 64
  title `Nomination in respect of deposits, bonds, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 30 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35302&sectionno=41B&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_41_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[41B. Nomination in respect of deposits, bonds, etc.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, where a nomination in respect of any deposits, bonds or other`
  line `securities is made in the prescribed manner, the amount due on such deposits, bonds or securities shall, on`
  line `the death of the depositor or holder thereof, vest in, and be payable to, the nominee subject to any right,`
  line `title or interest of any other person to such deposits, bonds or securities.`
  line
  line `(2) Any payment by the Financial Corporation in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall constitute a full discharge to the Financial Corporation of its liability in respect of such deposits,`
  line `bonds or securities.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (35303)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 65
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35303&sectionno=42&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, in any bill of lading, warehouse receipt or other document given to the`
  line `Financial Corporation, whereby security is given or is purported to be given to the Financial Corporation`
  line `for any accommodation granted by it under this Act, wilfully makes any false statement or knowingly`
  line `permits any false statement to be made shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, without the consent in writing of the Financial Corporation, uses the name of the`
  line `Financial Corporation in any prospectus or advertisement shall be punishable with imprisonment which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act otherwise than on a`
  line `complaint in writing signed by an officer of the Financial Corporation authorised by the Board in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (35304)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 66
  title `Provisions relating to income-tax and super-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35304&sectionno=43&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the ^1[Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961(43 of 1961)], the Financial Corporation shall be deemed to be a company within the meaning of that`
  line `Act and shall be liable to income-tax and super-tax accordingly on its income, profits and gains:`
  line
  line `Provided that any sum paid by the State Government under the guarantee given in pursuance`
  line `of^2*** ^3[section 7 or section 8] shall not be treated as the income, profits and gains of the Financial`
  line `Corporation and any interest on debentures, ^4[bonds or deposits] paid by the Financial Corporation out of`
  line `such sum shall not be treated as expenditure incurred by it:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any shareholder such portion of a dividend as has been paid out of`
  line `any such sum advanced by the State Government shall be deemed to be ^5[his] income from "interest on`
  line `securities"`
  line `^6[and the income-tax shall be payable thereon as if it were the interest receivable on any`
  line `security of a State Government issued income-tax free] within the meaning of section 8 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 26, for "Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figure "section 6 or" omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 31 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 22, for certain words (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "or bonds" (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and second Schedule, for "its" (w.e.f. 2-8-1952).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 6 of 1962, s. 22, for "Declared to be income-tax free" (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (35305)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 67
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35305&sectionno=43A&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Delegation of powers.--The Board may, by general or special order, delegate to the`
  line `managing director or to any other officer of the Financial Corporation ^2[or to any committee appointed`
  line `under section 21] subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order such`
  line `of its powers and duties under this Act as it may deem necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-4-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 27 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_b:
  sectionId (35306)
  sectionNo 43B
  orderNo 68
  title `Reports to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35306&sectionno=43B&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_43_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[43B. Reports to the Board.--(1) The minutes of every meeting of the committee appointed under`
  line `Section 21 shall, after confirmation thereof at the next meeting of the committee, be laid before the Board`
  line `at the next following meeting of the Board.`
  line
  line ^2*****.]
obj_root_law_sections_43_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 27 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 32 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (35307)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 69
  title `Act 18 of 1891 to apply to the books of the Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35307&sectionno=44&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Financial`
  line `Corporation shall be deemed to be a bank for the purposes of the Bankers Books Evidence Act, 1891`
  line `(18 of 1891).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (35308)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 70
  title `Liquidation of Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35308&sectionno=45&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies or corporations shall apply to the Financial Corporation, and the Financial Corporation shall`
  line `not be placed in liquidation, save by order of the State Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (35309)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to apply Act to certain financial institutions in existence at commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35309&sectionno=46&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, subject to such exceptions and restrictions as may be specified, apply to ^1[any`
  line `institution established by a State Government] which has for its object the financing of industrial`
  line `concerns, and on the issue of such notification, the institution shall be deemed to be a Financial`
  line `Corporation established by the State Government for the State within the meaning of this Act, and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall become applicable thereto according to the tenor of the notification:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no notification shall be issued under this sub-section in respect of any institution`
  line `unless a request is made in that behalf by the State Government concerned.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any notification issued under sub-section (1) may suspend the operation of any enactment`
  line `applicable to any such institution immediately before the issue of the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1985, s. 29, for "Any institution in existence at the commencement of this Act" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_a:
  sectionId (35310)
  sectionNo 46A
  orderNo 72
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of the Financial Corporation to other States by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35310&sectionno=46A&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_46_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[46A. Extension of jurisdiction of the Financial Corporation to other States by`
  line `agreement.-- (1) Where a Financial Corporation has been established for any State ^2`
  line `[and one or more`
  line `other States not served in whole or in part by a Financial Corporation] desires that the Financial`
  line `Corporation ^3[should serve the needs of those States or of any area therein], and the States, after`
  line `consultation with the ^4[Small Industries Bank], enter into an agreement which is published in the Official`
  line `Gazettes of each of those States, then the Financial Corporation shall, on the issue of a notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette by the Central Government, serve the needs of those States ^5[or, as the case may be, of`
  line `the area therein] in terms of the agreement ^5[and any Financial Corporation or any State may enter into`
  line `separate or successive agreements as aforesaid with one another or with other Financial Corporations of`
  line `States and in relation to different areas of the States].`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) Any agreement entered into under sub-section (1) may be modified or rescinded by mutual`
  line `agreement between the parties thereto and every such mutual agreement shall also provide for the`
  line `apportionment of assets and liabilities.]`
  line
  line `(2) An inter-State agreement among the participating States may, as far as may be, make all such`
  line `provisions as are referred to in sub-section (2) of section 3A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 27, for "and any other State" (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "should serve its needs" (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 33, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 27 (30-12-1972).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 27 (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_b:
  sectionId (35311)
  sectionNo 46B
  orderNo 73
  title `Effect of Act on other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1956, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35311&sectionno=46B&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_46_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[46B. Effect of Act on other laws.--The provision of this Act and of any rule or orders made`
  line `thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force or in the memorandum or articles of association of an industrial concern or in`
  line `any other instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act, but save as aforesaid, the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other law for the time being`
  line `applicable to an industrial concern.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (35324)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 74
  title `Omitted .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35324&sectionno=47&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `[Power of Board to make regulations.] Omitted by the State Financial Corporations (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2000 (39 of 2000), s. 34 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (35325)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35325&sectionno=48&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, after consultation with the ^1[Small`
  line `Industries Bank] and with the previous sanction of the State Government, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is`
  line `necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the holding and conduct of elections under this Act, including the final decision on doubts or`
  line `disputes regarding the validity of elections;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, the first allotment of the shares of`
  line `the Financial Corporation shall be made;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, the shares of the Financial`
  line `Corporation may be held and transferred and generally all matters relating to the rights and duties of`
  line shareholders;
  line
  line `^2[(ca) the maintenance of register of shareholders, particulars to be entered in such register, the`
  line `safeguards to be observed in the maintenance of register of shareholders on computer floppies or`
  line `diskettes, compact disk or any other electronic form the inspection and closure of the register of`
  line `shareholders and all other matters connected therewith under section 6;`
  line
  line `(cb) the manner of nomination of directors under clause (d) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(cc) the entrusting or delegation of duties to the managing director by the Board under clause (c)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(cd) the functions of Executive Committee under sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(ce) the guidelines and prudential norms in accordance with which investment may be made`
  line `under section 34;`
  line
  line `(cf) the manner in which nomination may be made under section 4IB; and`
  line
  line `(cg) the investments (whether by way of deposits in bank or otherwise) of the amounts which are`
  line `not for the time being required for transaction of business;]`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which general meetings shall be convened, the procedure to be followed thereat`
  line `and the manner in which voting rights may be exercised;`
  line
  line `(e) the calling of meetings of the Board, and of the Executive Committee, fees for attending`
  line `meetings thereof and the conduct of business thereat;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner and terms of issue and repayment of bonds and debentures by the Financial`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(g) the conditions which the Financial Corporation may impose in granting loans or advances;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) the forms of returns and statements required under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) the duties and conduct of officers, other employees, advisers and agents of the Financial`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(k) the establishment and maintenance of provident or other benefit funds for employees of the`
  line `Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(l) the taking over of the management of any industrial concern on a breach of its agreement with`
  line `the Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(m) the appointment of ^4[committees] for the purposes of this Act, ^5[fees for attending meetings`
  line `thereof and the conduct of business thereat]; and`
  line
  line `(n) generally, the efficient conduct of the affairs of the Financial Corporation.`
  line
  line `^6[(o) the form and manner in which the balance-sheet and the accounts of the Financial`
  line `Corporation shall be prepared;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^7[(3) All regulations made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette and any such`
  line `regulation shall have effect from such earlier or later date as may be specified in the regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 35, for "Development Bank" (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 43 of 1985, s. 30 (w.e.f. 21-8-1985)`
  line `4 Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "advisory committees for technical and other advice" (w.e.f. 21-8-1985).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by act 56 of 1956, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-10-1956).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 39 of 2000, s. 35 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by Act 77 of 1972, s. 28, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 30-12-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_a:
  sectionId (35313)
  sectionNo 48A
  orderNo 76
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before State Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35313&sectionno=48A&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[48A. Laying of rules and regulations before State Legislature. ----^2`
  line `*** and every regulation`
  line `made under section 48 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. The words "Every rule made under section 47 and" omitted by Act 39 of 2000, s. 36 (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_b:
  sectionId (35314)
  sectionNo 48B
  orderNo 77
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35314&sectionno=48B&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[48B. Power to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may`
  line `provide for the procedure for filing and hearing of appeals under sub-section (5) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (35315)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 78
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456&sectionId=35315&sectionno=49&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00043_195163_1517807325456
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, as amended by the Public Financial Institutions Laws (Amendment) Act, 1975 (52 of 1975), the`
  line `Central Government may, by order, do anything, not inconsistent with such provisions, for the purpose of`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of three years from the`
  line `commencement of the said Amendment Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
